# codeowners defines who can approve changes to specific paths.
# learn more: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
# 
# each line: pattern @owner
# - use team names (@org/team-name) for groups
# - multiple owners = anyone on the list can approve
# - order matters — last match wins for conflicts
#
# examples:
# organisation.md @your-org/leadership
# CONTEXT/decisions.md @your-org/leadership
# CONTEXT/ @your-org/team

# default owners (everyone in the org)
* @your-org/engineering

# core context — requires leadership approval
organisation.md @your-org/leadership

# context files — team-wide
CONTEXT/ @your-org/team

# infrastructure — ops team
.github/workflows/ @your-org/ops
